author: BRIAN ROKOS
title: JURUPA VALLEY: Suicidal man prompts neighborhood warning
text:
By BRIAN ROKOS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 12, 2015 Updated: 4:05 p.m. JURUPA VALLEY: Suicidal man prompts neighborhood warning Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» People in a neighborhood in western Jurupa Valley were urged to stay inside early Monday afternoon, Oct. 12, as Riverside County sheriff's deputies tried to coax a suicidal man into surrendering.
Deputies received a report about 12:40 p.m. of a man threatening to harm himself in the 10500 block of Cantu-Galleano Ranch Road, Deputy Armando Munoz said. The man apparently had some type of weapon.
The incident is near Jurupa Valley High, but that school was not on lockdown, an employee there said.
